WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.270 --> 00:00:05.190
<b>25 Years Ago</b>

3
00:00:01.770 --> 00:00:05.320
Turn back the clock twenty-five years...

4
00:00:13.540 --> 00:00:18.500
Shortly before the dawn
of the Great Pirate Era...

5
00:00:51.240 --> 00:00:54.450
Are you louts enjoyin' yourselves?!

6
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:00.500
Alright!

7
00:01:00.500 --> 00:01:02.830
I am glad I accompanied you...

8
00:01:03.170 --> 00:01:04.340
Roger!

9
00:01:04.340 --> 00:01:08.170
Huh?! What's gotten into you, idiot?!

10
00:01:12.640 --> 00:01:13.640
Oden!

11
00:01:14.050 --> 00:01:17.390
We should be thanking you!

12
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:26.360
You're drinking too much, Roger!

13
00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:27.780
Control yourself!

14
00:01:29.440 --> 00:01:30.610
Shut it!

15
00:01:30.610 --> 00:01:33.200
As if I'd take advice from a drunken doctor!

16
00:01:35.580 --> 00:01:38.660
I'm concerned about your health!

17
00:01:39.540 --> 00:01:40.750
You bastard!

18
00:01:41.750 --> 00:01:43.750
That's how you cure stupidity.

19
00:01:43.750 --> 00:01:44.750
Shut your trap!

20
00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:48.760
Damn you!

21
00:02:00.020 --> 00:02:02.770
I must go back...

22
00:02:02.770 --> 00:02:03.980
To Wano?

23
00:02:04.650 --> 00:02:05.810
Yes.

24
00:02:05.810 --> 00:02:07.860
I left a crucial task behind.

25
00:02:08.610 --> 00:02:12.820
Is there anything we can do to help, Oden?

26
00:02:12.820 --> 00:02:14.660
If you need a hand...

27
00:02:14.660 --> 00:02:17.950
I don't mind lending you one, Oden!

28
00:02:17.950 --> 00:02:19.160
You dummy!

29
00:02:19.160 --> 00:02:21.580
You'll just get in his way!

30
00:02:21.580 --> 00:02:25.250
Hey, Oden! I'm sure I could help!

31
00:02:28.090 --> 00:02:29.300
Rayleigh...

32
00:02:29.300 --> 00:02:31.420
Redtaro and Buggyjiro...

33
00:02:32.420 --> 00:02:34.010
You have my thanks!

34
00:02:34.010 --> 00:02:35.260
However...

35
00:02:37.510 --> 00:02:40.350
this duty lies with the Kozuki alone.

36
00:02:40.350 --> 00:02:44.060
I've asked so many times,
why am I "jiro" as if I'm the second son?

37
00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:46.270
Let it go!

38
00:02:47.230 --> 00:02:50.110
Gotcha. The Kozuki, huh?

39
00:02:50.110 --> 00:02:53.570
I learned much throughout this voyage...

40
00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:58.370
I had always wondered why
Wano closed its doors.

41
00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:01.490
I left imprudently,

42
00:03:01.490 --> 00:03:06.580
so it would be far too selfish to demand
I be appointed the next shogun of Wano.

43
00:03:08.210 --> 00:03:11.090
But I must pass on my will at any cost!

44
00:03:15.300 --> 00:03:19.350
With the aid of my exceptional
retainers that I left behind,

45
00:03:19.350 --> 00:03:21.890
I will open the borders of Wano,

46
00:03:22.560 --> 00:03:26.730
and I shall await a future that will come
more than twenty years from now!

47
00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:31.320
Let's do it, Oden!

48
00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:32.730
Yes!

49
00:03:32.730 --> 00:03:35.240
We shall, Roger!

50
00:03:39.490 --> 00:03:43.120
Now, twenty-five years have passed.

51
00:03:40.120 --> 00:03:43.120
<b>25 Years Later</b>

52
00:03:47.160 --> 00:03:48.240
<b>Act 3</b>
<b>Wano</b>

53
00:03:56.010 --> 00:03:57.800
What a perfect day for a banquet.

54
00:03:57.800 --> 00:04:02.430
The weather itself even favors our lord, Orochi.

55
00:04:02.640 --> 00:04:06.140
This year, Kyoshiro is remaining
to supervise the capital.

56
00:04:06.140 --> 00:04:07.690
Tell him we appreciate it!

57
00:04:07.690 --> 00:04:08.940
Yes, sir!

58
00:04:08.940 --> 00:04:10.230
Poor guy!

59
00:04:10.230 --> 00:04:13.440
To think he can't attend the banquet!

60
00:04:13.440 --> 00:04:20.110
Habu Port in Hakumai is known
as the largest port in Wano.

61
00:04:20.990 --> 00:04:27.790
Maple trees line the giant pier
which projects from the shore into the sea,

62
00:04:27.790 --> 00:04:32.920
and the lovely scene of
fluttering red leaves sends ships off.

63
00:04:35.300 --> 00:04:37.300
It's a wonderful day!

64
00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:41.510
Fetch some sake! Let's have a cup
while admiring those red leaves!

65
00:04:41.510 --> 00:04:45.220
Lord Orochi, you should abstain
until we reach Lord Kaido...

66
00:04:45.890 --> 00:04:49.020
Who cares?! I'm sure he's already drunk, too!

67
00:04:49.560 --> 00:04:52.060
It's a massive banquet with
30,000 attendees!

68
00:04:52.060 --> 00:04:54.940
Let's have a blast as always!

69
00:04:54.940 --> 00:04:57.900
Once a year, on the night of the Fire Festival,

70
00:04:58.280 --> 00:05:02.030
the two leaders who rule over Wano
come together at Onigashima.

71
00:05:02.740 --> 00:05:07.500
They throw a huge banquet for
the combined armies of Orochi and Kaido.

72
00:05:11.160 --> 00:05:14.030
Open up the borderless map, then

73
00:05:14.030 --> 00:05:17.230
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

74
00:05:17.230 --> 00:05:21.620
LET’S SAIL ON right now, hoist your sails up high

75
00:05:21.620 --> 00:05:24.610
Riding on the wind

76
00:05:29.740 --> 00:05:33.950
DON’T GIVE UP, it’s time to finish what we started

77
00:05:34.140 --> 00:05:36.920
So don't you grow disheartened

78
00:05:37.230 --> 00:05:40.680
Laugh the tears away through the storm

79
00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:45.110
SHOUT IT OUT, when you feel down always remember

80
00:05:45.450 --> 00:05:47.710
That’s what your friends are there for

81
00:05:47.740 --> 00:05:49.870
Y’know there’s no point in fronting,

82
00:05:49.870 --> 00:05:53.790
your crew will always have your back

83
00:05:54.160 --> 00:05:57.890
Even in the face of utter darkness

84
00:05:58.120 --> 00:06:00.880
C’mon, BRAVE IT OUT We’ll be alright

85
00:06:01.180 --> 00:06:04.670
Together you know that we’ll never lose a fight

86
00:06:04.890 --> 00:06:07.660
Open up the borderless map, then

87
00:06:07.680 --> 00:06:10.520
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

88
00:06:10.820 --> 00:06:15.100
All great journeys starts with a single step

89
00:06:15.170 --> 00:06:16.110
DREAMIN’ ON

90
00:06:16.110 --> 00:06:18.890
Open up the borderless map, then

91
00:06:18.890 --> 00:06:21.630
Raise the flag we swore to defend

92
00:06:21.780 --> 00:06:24.520
We’ll never stop until we’ve reached the top

93
00:06:24.590 --> 00:06:28.990
Just be true to yourself until the end

94
00:06:29.120 --> 00:06:33.830
Set sail and grab it, DREAMIN ON

95
00:06:42.840 --> 00:06:45.380
<b>Flower

Capital</b>

96
00:06:43.970 --> 00:06:45.380
<b>The Day

of the

Fire

Festival</b>

97
00:06:45.430 --> 00:06:51.390
<b>The Designated Port</b>

98
00:06:49.100 --> 00:06:50.770
Drink up! Drink up!

99
00:06:51.390 --> 00:06:53.430
Come on! Dance!

100
00:06:53.430 --> 00:06:56.150
Drink! Sing!

101
00:06:56.150 --> 00:06:59.190
It's the Fire Festival in the capital today!

102
00:06:59.190 --> 00:07:01.440
It's the one day a year we're allowed to drink!

103
00:07:01.440 --> 00:07:04.280
Let's really drink hard and let loose today!

104
00:07:04.280 --> 00:07:06.570
Hurry up! It's already started!

105
00:07:06.570 --> 00:07:08.910
Hold on! I can't get my bangs to behave!

106
00:07:12.910 --> 00:07:14.210
Oh...?

107
00:07:14.210 --> 00:07:18.920
The sky's so clear! The full moon
will look so beautiful tonight!

108
00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:37.690
<b>Tokage
 Port</b>
<b>Hakumai</b>

109
00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:30.420
<b>Kibi</b>

110
00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:30.220
<b>Kuri Flower 
Capital</b>

111
00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:30.760
<b>Ringo</b>

112
00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:37.680
<b>Udon</b>

113
00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:30.640
<b>Wano Country</b>

114
00:07:25.800 --> 00:07:30.760
The seasons differ wildly in each region of Wano,

115
00:07:30.220 --> 00:07:30.510
<b>Flower 
Capital</b>

116
00:07:30.220 --> 00:07:30.550
<b>Kuri</b>

117
00:07:30.220 --> 00:07:30.840
<b>Udon Hakumai</b>

118
00:07:30.260 --> 00:07:30.380
<b>Kibi Flower 
Capital</b>

119
00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:30.470
<b>Kuri Kibi</b>

120
00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:37.690
but the weather also varies
tremendously by location.

121
00:07:39.940 --> 00:07:41.190
At that same moment,

122
00:07:41.190 --> 00:07:43.030
at the rendezvous point,

123
00:07:43.030 --> 00:07:44.610
Tokage Port...

124
00:08:11.550 --> 00:08:13.600
Not a single ship is in sight!

125
00:08:14.770 --> 00:08:16.730
Where are our 4,000 warriors?!

126
00:08:18.140 --> 00:08:21.610
I am positive we conquered Udon!

127
00:08:25.320 --> 00:08:29.570
But there was no one
at the mining camp, either.

128
00:08:29.570 --> 00:08:32.660
This port shows signs of an attack!

129
00:08:33.240 --> 00:08:35.540
It appears the cat couldn't make it.

130
00:08:42.460 --> 00:08:44.300
No response on the smail.

131
00:08:45.210 --> 00:08:48.090
We cannot contact anyone!

132
00:08:51.840 --> 00:08:55.810
"At twilight on the day of
the Fire Festival, at Tokage Port!"

133
00:08:57.890 --> 00:09:01.270
This is the rendezvous port!

134
00:09:01.270 --> 00:09:04.980
Why has no one arrived?!
Just where did they disappear to?

135
00:09:08.360 --> 00:09:10.530
It has been but a single day...!

136
00:09:11.110 --> 00:09:13.030
What is the meaning of this?!

137
00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:15.790
Did something befall them?!

138
00:09:19.540 --> 00:09:22.330
Sir Luffy, where are you?!

139
00:09:22.330 --> 00:09:24.710
Sir Hyogoro, please respond!

140
00:09:29.840 --> 00:09:31.720
Inuarashi’s Musketeers!

141
00:09:31.720 --> 00:09:32.930
Sir Law!

142
00:09:32.930 --> 00:09:34.390
Jibuemon of Kibi!

143
00:09:34.390 --> 00:09:38.350
We are Kozuki Oden's retainers!

144
00:09:38.680 --> 00:09:40.770
From twenty years ago...

145
00:09:43.730 --> 00:09:49.740
We came from twenty years ago
to avenge our lord!

146
00:09:49.740 --> 00:09:52.950
We were meant to perish at that time!

147
00:09:52.950 --> 00:09:55.570
So we came to die for a cause!

148
00:09:58.620 --> 00:09:59.790
However...

149
00:10:00.290 --> 00:10:03.120
However, I fear our lives alone are not enough!

150
00:10:03.120 --> 00:10:06.500
The enemy has 30,000 warriors!
We need your support!

151
00:10:08.550 --> 00:10:09.590
I am begging you!

152
00:10:09.590 --> 00:10:12.800
Somebody, please help us!

153
00:10:12.800 --> 00:10:14.590
Please respond! Anybody!

154
00:10:14.930 --> 00:10:17.430
Please help!

155
00:10:15.430 --> 00:10:17.430
Enough, Kin'emon!

156
00:10:20.310 --> 00:10:23.060
Look at the sky and sea!

157
00:10:23.940 --> 00:10:27.570
Even the heavens have already abandoned us!

158
00:10:27.570 --> 00:10:29.820
No one is coming to help us!

159
00:10:29.820 --> 00:10:33.610
Something must have happened to everyone...

160
00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:40.620
Heave ho! Heave ho! Heave ho!

161
00:10:41.450 --> 00:10:43.040
Dance! Dance!

162
00:10:43.040 --> 00:10:45.580
It's the annual Fire Festival!

163
00:10:45.580 --> 00:10:50.750
Why don't you let loose
and blow off some steam tonight?!

164
00:10:55.130 --> 00:10:57.300
There is a small boat over here...

165
00:10:57.300 --> 00:10:58.760
We can use it.

166
00:10:59.350 --> 00:11:01.270
What are you doing, Inuarashi?!

167
00:11:01.270 --> 00:11:02.810
Stop it!

168
00:11:03.310 --> 00:11:05.520
Let us do this another day, Kin'emon!

169
00:11:05.520 --> 00:11:09.190
That is a request... I cannot fulfill.

170
00:11:14.610 --> 00:11:15.820
Master Kin!

171
00:11:17.820 --> 00:11:19.780
Let go of me, Shinobu!

172
00:11:22.160 --> 00:11:24.710
Master Kin, we cannot do this tonight!

173
00:11:25.250 --> 00:11:27.580
We must do it tonight!

174
00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:30.590
You know that, Shinobu.

175
00:11:36.970 --> 00:11:38.930
<b>Onigashima</b>

176
00:11:39.890 --> 00:11:41.970
It has got to be tonight!

177
00:11:47.940 --> 00:11:52.520
Something had indeed
happened the previous night.

178
00:11:52.520 --> 00:11:56.950
<b>Two Days Ago</b>

179
00:11:53.150 --> 00:11:56.990
Turn the clock back two days
before the Fire Festival...

180
00:11:56.110 --> 00:11:59.450
<b>Amigasa 

Village</b>

181
00:12:00.200 --> 00:12:03.950
Mm-hm. We now have 4,200 warriors.

182
00:12:03.950 --> 00:12:07.210
I am grateful... truly grateful
that they joined us!

183
00:12:08.080 --> 00:12:09.290
Everyone!

184
00:12:09.830 --> 00:12:11.920
Thank you for all your efforts!

185
00:12:12.250 --> 00:12:15.550
Use the remaining time to get
into position and prepare.

186
00:12:16.550 --> 00:12:17.550
Well then...

187
00:12:17.550 --> 00:12:20.390
See you at the rendezvous port!

188
00:12:24.680 --> 00:12:28.390
<b>Itachi Port


Kuri</b>

189
00:12:28.940 --> 00:12:32.900
Finish fixing enough ships
to carry 5,000 people!

190
00:12:32.900 --> 00:12:33.860
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

191
00:12:33.860 --> 00:12:38.740
Bring those ships to the port by
the appointed time! Can you handle that?

192
00:12:39.070 --> 00:12:41.530
Leave it to us, Big Bro Franosuke!

193
00:12:41.530 --> 00:12:42.950
Alright!

194
00:12:42.950 --> 00:12:47.160
Then, we'll meet up with our friends
in Amigasa Village,

195
00:12:42.970 --> 00:12:47.160
<b>Itachi

Port</b>
<b>Amigasa

Village</b>

196
00:12:47.580 --> 00:12:50.830
and arrive via the Sunny on the promised day!

197
00:12:50.830 --> 00:12:52.460
We'll leave the rest to you!

198
00:12:52.460 --> 00:12:55.170
Yeah! Thanks for helping out!

199
00:12:55.170 --> 00:12:57.380
You guys are top-notch shipwrights!

200
00:12:57.380 --> 00:13:00.840
Thanks! Let's give those Beast Pirates...

201
00:13:01.840 --> 00:13:04.810
...an ass-kicking they won't forget!

202
00:13:08.890 --> 00:13:13.110
<b>Udon</b>
No matter how much timber we have,
it's never enough! Cut up everything!

203
00:13:13.110 --> 00:13:17.440
Ocho's group will bring swords
and other weapons from Ringo!

204
00:13:17.440 --> 00:13:18.530
So...

205
00:13:18.530 --> 00:13:21.320
We'll craft armor from whatever we have!

206
00:13:21.320 --> 00:13:22.910
I don't know if they're usable,

207
00:13:22.910 --> 00:13:26.990
but we've got tons of stuff that was
made for export, even weapons!

208
00:13:26.990 --> 00:13:28.500
Excellent!

209
00:13:28.500 --> 00:13:34.130
<b>Kibi</b>

210
00:13:28.500 --> 00:13:33.420
We'll draw attention if we travel
to the rendezvous point too early.

211
00:13:33.420 --> 00:13:34.130
But...

212
00:13:34.130 --> 00:13:39.010
<b>Habu

Port</b>
on the morning in question, the shogun's procession
will journey from the capital to the port.
<b>Flower

Capital</b>

213
00:13:39.010 --> 00:13:43.640
Once they leave for Onigashima,
the Fire Festival will commence in the capital!

214
00:13:43.640 --> 00:13:46.510
No one will pay us any mind!

215
00:13:46.510 --> 00:13:47.930
"Two birds..."

216
00:13:46.510 --> 00:13:51.390
<b>Udon</b>

217
00:13:47.930 --> 00:13:51.390
We had best arrive before twilight.

218
00:13:51.390 --> 00:13:54.860
<b>Itachi

Port</b>
Some officials, however,
will remain on the mainland!

219
00:13:54.860 --> 00:13:59.230
<b>Kibi</b>
We cannot let them report
to Onigashima, so stay alert the whole way!

220
00:13:59.230 --> 00:14:00.360
– Okay!
– Okay!

221
00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:07.870
Can we really wear these?!

222
00:14:07.870 --> 00:14:11.910
Wow! It's a samurai helmet!
I've gotta show this to Usopp!

223
00:14:11.910 --> 00:14:14.040
We're warriors!

224
00:14:19.050 --> 00:14:21.380
Your enemy is that ill-famed Kaido.

225
00:14:22.010 --> 00:14:24.390
Are you all prepared?!

226
00:14:24.390 --> 00:14:25.760
Kaido?

227
00:14:26.260 --> 00:14:27.260
That loser...

228
00:14:28.350 --> 00:14:30.430
is about to get sliced 'n diced!

229
00:14:31.480 --> 00:14:34.100
It's inconceivable that we would lose!

230
00:14:34.100 --> 00:14:35.980
Bring it on!

231
00:14:39.360 --> 00:14:41.490
Chobro and the others look so cool!

232
00:14:41.490 --> 00:14:44.410
Oh, how cute. Just like bugs.

233
00:14:44.410 --> 00:14:47.160
Shouldn't you wear some armor, too?

234
00:14:47.160 --> 00:14:49.370
No, it'll just slow me down.

235
00:14:49.370 --> 00:14:50.790
Wear it.

236
00:14:51.250 --> 00:14:54.330
With a bounty that low, you'll be needing it.

237
00:14:54.330 --> 00:14:55.080
Enma!

238
00:15:02.050 --> 00:15:05.300
You want some of this?
I'll snuff the life outta you!

239
00:15:05.300 --> 00:15:07.220
Try it, you bastard!

240
00:15:09.970 --> 00:15:12.020
What are you morons doing?!

241
00:15:15.100 --> 00:15:19.360
Orochi mentioned it's winter
at Onigashima's entrance.

242
00:15:19.360 --> 00:15:21.530
What? It'll be cold?

243
00:15:21.530 --> 00:15:23.990
What do you mean by "entrance"?

244
00:15:23.990 --> 00:15:27.910
The seasons in Wano vary
depending on region.

245
00:15:27.910 --> 00:15:31.240
Our fur coats help us withstand the cold.

246
00:15:31.240 --> 00:15:34.000
<b>Inuarashi's Three Musketeers</b>

247
00:15:31.240 --> 00:15:34.250
Yeah, for us, the weather is more crucial...

248
00:15:33.250 --> 00:15:36.210
<b>Giovanni</b>
<b>Concelot</b>
<b>Shishilian</b>

249
00:15:34.250 --> 00:15:35.660
...than the season!

250
00:15:36.210 --> 00:15:41.000
There's supposed to be a full moon that night,
but it's useless if it's hidden behind the clouds.

251
00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:42.550
That's right!

252
00:15:42.550 --> 00:15:46.550
If all the minks can transform like Carrot,
that'll be a huge advantage!

253
00:15:54.890 --> 00:15:57.310
– Garchu!
– Garchu!

254
00:15:57.310 --> 00:16:01.230
<b>Wanda</b>

255
00:15:57.730 --> 00:16:01.230
But we still require luck, even with the Sulong form.

256
00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:06.530
It's more crucial that Master Nekomamushi
and his Guardians make it here.

257
00:16:11.870 --> 00:16:13.370
What's wrong, Luffy?

258
00:16:17.660 --> 00:16:19.540
Big Mom is here...

259
00:16:21.340 --> 00:16:24.050
but not Jinbe!

260
00:16:24.050 --> 00:16:27.840
Thanks to him, we got away from Big Mom!

261
00:16:30.010 --> 00:16:32.050
I'll wait for you in Wano!

262
00:16:32.050 --> 00:16:33.510
You better be there!

263
00:16:35.350 --> 00:16:36.980
You have my gratitude!

264
00:16:36.980 --> 00:16:38.390
Jinbe!

265
00:16:39.650 --> 00:16:41.810
Don't die no matter what!

266
00:16:48.070 --> 00:16:51.570
He settled things and joined our crew!

267
00:17:01.750 --> 00:17:03.290
We're happy to have him...

268
00:17:03.290 --> 00:17:06.300
We've still got time... He'll come!

269
00:17:06.300 --> 00:17:08.130
If he's alive, that is.

270
00:17:08.550 --> 00:17:10.380
He's alive! I'm sure!

271
00:17:12.390 --> 00:17:13.300
He'll come!

272
00:17:14.600 --> 00:17:19.430
<b>Ebisu Town


Outside of

 the Flower Capital</b>

273
00:17:15.430 --> 00:17:19.430
Hey, everyone! Look at this!
The Witching Hour Boy was here!

274
00:17:19.430 --> 00:17:22.400
But there's no talk of a robbery in the capital!

275
00:17:22.400 --> 00:17:26.190
There's nobody else
who would do something like this!

276
00:17:26.190 --> 00:17:31.110
We can't attend the tomorrow's Fire Festival,
but let's use this to purchase drinking water!

277
00:17:31.910 --> 00:17:34.740
We burned down the mountain bandits' home!

278
00:17:35.120 --> 00:17:38.200
But instead of coming here to seek revenge,

279
00:17:38.200 --> 00:17:42.250
<b>Okobore

Town


Kuri</b>
they continue to steal
tons of food from our farm!

280
00:17:42.250 --> 00:17:44.210
<b>Headliner Holdem

Beast Pirates</b>

281
00:17:44.840 --> 00:17:48.840
Do any of you have
something to do with this?!

282
00:17:48.840 --> 00:17:50.420
W-We don't know anything!

283
00:17:50.840 --> 00:17:54.340
I heard some samurai are preparing for a raid!

284
00:17:54.340 --> 00:17:56.720
Could that be why?

285
00:17:56.720 --> 00:17:58.810
If so, we can't let them know!

286
00:17:59.930 --> 00:18:02.350
What are you swine whispering about?!

287
00:18:03.940 --> 00:18:06.150
I will show you where it is!

288
00:18:06.150 --> 00:18:09.440
<b>Otsuru

Kin'emon's Wife</b>

289
00:18:06.480 --> 00:18:09.440
In exchange, please do not harm anyone.

290
00:18:09.440 --> 00:18:10.940
M-Miss Otsuru!

291
00:18:10.940 --> 00:18:12.360
You'll show me?

292
00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:16.370
You know something about this?

293
00:18:16.700 --> 00:18:18.240
You will see once we arrive.

294
00:18:18.240 --> 00:18:19.830
It is a little far though...

295
00:18:26.340 --> 00:18:30.210
You must need all that food
because you have gathered so many allies!

296
00:18:31.090 --> 00:18:32.470
Right, Kin?

297
00:18:32.970 --> 00:18:35.760
You're here in Wano, right?

298
00:18:36.510 --> 00:18:39.100
I was astounded when I saw Kikunojo!

299
00:18:42.180 --> 00:18:43.310
Kin...

300
00:18:44.020 --> 00:18:46.520
Kin, let me handle things here!

301
00:18:46.520 --> 00:18:48.770
I will draw their attention!

302
00:18:48.770 --> 00:18:51.530
I will not allow them to search for you!

303
00:18:52.530 --> 00:18:57.370
Kin... Return this country to the Kozuki!

304
00:18:58.700 --> 00:19:00.330
Stop, Miss Otsuru!

305
00:19:00.330 --> 00:19:02.250
You don't have to cover for us!

306
00:19:02.580 --> 00:19:04.120
It's okay now!

307
00:19:04.120 --> 00:19:07.420
We just wanted to eat our fill before we die!

308
00:19:07.420 --> 00:19:08.590
What?

309
00:19:08.590 --> 00:19:10.130
Huh?!

310
00:19:10.130 --> 00:19:12.800
So you're the culprits!

311
00:19:15.680 --> 00:19:19.890
<b>Night 

Before

the Great 

Battle</b>

312
00:19:19.890 --> 00:19:22.270
Red Scabbards...

313
00:19:23.270 --> 00:19:26.020
I'm going to show you the depths of hell!

314
00:19:28.060 --> 00:19:30.820
<b>Kuri

Beach</b>

315
00:19:28.440 --> 00:19:30.190
Did you find the ship?

316
00:19:30.190 --> 00:19:30.820
Yes.

317
00:19:31.530 --> 00:19:33.280
We found it.

318
00:19:34.110 --> 00:19:35.860
You sure about this?

319
00:19:36.240 --> 00:19:39.830
Don't question me!

320
00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:43.040
Do it!

321
00:19:43.580 --> 00:19:44.620
Roger!

322
00:20:00.140 --> 00:20:01.350
Mission complete!

323
00:20:06.100 --> 00:20:09.770
I won't let you have your way!

324
00:20:10.230 --> 00:20:12.400
Next, the bridges!

325
00:20:12.690 --> 00:20:17.360
<b>Great

 Kibi-Udon 

Bridge</b>

326
00:20:14.320 --> 00:20:17.360
Detonation complete
on the great Kibi-Udon bridge!

327
00:20:17.360 --> 00:20:19.240
Destroy them!

328
00:20:19.490 --> 00:20:24.290
<b>Great

Kuri-Udon

Bridge</b>

329
00:20:21.240 --> 00:20:24.290
Detonation complete
on the great Kuri-Udon bridge!

330
00:20:24.290 --> 00:20:26.370
Serves them right!

331
00:20:26.830 --> 00:20:30.710
<b>Great

Ringo-Hakumai

Bridge</b>

332
00:20:28.290 --> 00:20:30.710
Look! The great bridge between the regions...!

333
00:20:31.080 --> 00:20:32.670
Why now?!

334
00:20:32.670 --> 00:20:35.800
We cannot get to the other side now!

335
00:20:35.800 --> 00:20:38.340
All that remains is the port!

336
00:20:40.300 --> 00:20:45.970
<b>Itachi Port

Kuri</b>

337
00:20:40.720 --> 00:20:43.390
Lord Orochi! All ships have been destroyed!

338
00:20:43.390 --> 00:20:47.810
That's fine. We'll rebuild
once the dust has settled.

339
00:20:48.690 --> 00:20:55.610
I have yet to see the Red Scabbards
or their samurai recruits with my own eyes.

340
00:20:56.030 --> 00:21:01.070
People skipped forward in time
from twenty years ago?!

341
00:21:01.660 --> 00:21:04.240
How could anyone believe that?!

342
00:21:04.950 --> 00:21:08.120
Maybe if they saw one of their heads...

343
00:21:08.580 --> 00:21:13.630
No, even if they saw it, they'd never believe it.

344
00:21:13.630 --> 00:21:20.130
And that damn fool, Yasuie,
made it sound even more ridiculous!

345
00:21:20.680 --> 00:21:23.140
But the information is credible.

346
00:21:23.640 --> 00:21:25.760
The Red Scabbards...

347
00:21:25.760 --> 00:21:27.520
still draw breath!

348
00:21:29.600 --> 00:21:33.980
I don't care if my men think I'm crazy.

349
00:21:33.980 --> 00:21:37.820
I have the authority to take action!

350
00:21:38.280 --> 00:21:43.700
I've blocked all possible routes to Tokage Port.

351
00:21:39.440 --> 00:21:43.690
<b>Kibi</b>
<b>Ringo</b>
<b>Kuri</b>
<b>Flower 





Capital</b>
<b>Udon</b>
<b>Hakumai</b>
<b>Tokage 
Port</b>

352
00:21:44.240 --> 00:21:47.870
Four thousand warriors? It's very impressive, recruiting so many.

353
00:21:47.870 --> 00:21:51.790
But none will make it to the port!

354
00:21:52.710 --> 00:21:56.590
I won't give them even
the slimmest chance at taking revenge!

355
00:21:58.760 --> 00:22:01.590
Go to hell, Red Scabbard specters!

356
00:22:01.930 --> 00:22:07.260
Wallow in the despair of
isolation and impotence!

357
00:22:11.600 --> 00:22:14.310
<b>Present Day


Tokage Port

Udon</b>

358
00:22:15.020 --> 00:22:16.820
Stop, all of you!

359
00:22:16.820 --> 00:22:19.780
Taking that small boat is suicide!

360
00:22:21.530 --> 00:22:25.820
Let us regroup and begin anew
when we get another chance!

361
00:22:25.820 --> 00:22:28.120
If we miss this opportunity...

362
00:22:29.080 --> 00:22:31.540
we will have to wait a whole year.

363
00:22:32.870 --> 00:22:39.420
But... we cannot hide any longer.
They will soon learn how we liberated Udon.

364
00:22:40.340 --> 00:22:45.180
Kaido's entire army
will descend to hunt the rebels,

365
00:22:47.220 --> 00:22:51.220
and we can no longer continue
to steal their food.

366
00:22:51.220 --> 00:22:55.400
Before we departed Kuri,
you surely heard what happened.

367
00:22:56.730 --> 00:23:01.610
The people of Okobore Town,
who believed in our great struggle...

368
00:23:01.610 --> 00:23:03.280
were burned alive.

369
00:23:04.150 --> 00:23:05.530
Among them...

370
00:23:06.490 --> 00:23:08.070
was my wife.

371
00:23:11.330 --> 00:23:13.040
Please allow us to go!

372
00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:17.170
No...!

373
00:23:17.170 --> 00:23:22.670
Do you want us to flee and live in disgrace?!

374
00:23:23.760 --> 00:23:26.260
And what of me...?

375
00:23:26.260 --> 00:23:30.390
We want you to live on with Princess Hiyori!

376
00:23:30.390 --> 00:23:32.640
Do not be so selfish!

377
00:23:34.350 --> 00:23:37.810
Even your father had no support at first!

378
00:23:37.810 --> 00:23:41.820
If we had not met Lord Oden...

379
00:23:41.820 --> 00:23:46.740
...we would not have become samurai,
immature as we were.

380
00:23:47.160 --> 00:23:49.870
That is why we want to be...

381
00:23:50.530 --> 00:23:55.500
Lord Oden's samurai retainers...
until the very end.

382
00:23:56.920 --> 00:23:58.330
Do not go!

383
00:23:58.670 --> 00:24:00.500
Do not go, Kin'emon!

384
00:24:00.500 --> 00:24:02.750
Do not go!

385
00:24:02.750 --> 00:24:06.170
I cannot bear to lose even one more person!

386
00:24:09.010 --> 00:24:11.010
Listen, men!

387
00:24:11.550 --> 00:24:18.520
This centuries-old policy of national isolation
is deeply tied to the Kozuki Clan.

388
00:24:19.270 --> 00:24:20.480
However...

389
00:24:21.230 --> 00:24:23.320
the time will eventually come!

390
00:24:24.070 --> 00:24:27.570
Before the tides begin to turn worldwide,

391
00:24:27.570 --> 00:24:30.410
we must open the borders of Wano!

392
00:24:53.430 --> 00:24:58.520
Forty-one years ago, in the Flower Capital...

393
00:24:59.980 --> 00:25:02.810
Kozuki Oden has returned!

394
00:25:03.230 --> 00:25:04.440
Hide your wives!

395
00:25:04.440 --> 00:25:06.190
Your daughters, too...!

396
00:25:06.650 --> 00:25:08.320
Even the livestock!

397
00:25:11.660 --> 00:25:14.410
He failed to set sail again!

398
00:25:14.410 --> 00:25:16.580
He wants to get out of here that badly?!

399
00:25:17.870 --> 00:25:22.880
There was a very popular man in the capital.

400
00:25:34.680 --> 00:25:37.640
It is so restrictive!
